name: ExclusionForStrokeAndTransientIschemicAttack
title: Exclusion for Stroke and Transient Ischemic Attack
description: This value set is created for MSSP ACO-38 Risk-Standardized Acute Admission Rates for Patients with Multiple Chronic Conditions measure and represents the EXCLUSION value set for the chronic condition of Stroke and Transient Ischemic Attack (TIA).  If any of the qualifying claims have any of the following codes in any DX position then EXCLUDE.  There is a second EXCLUSION value set Z51.89 as the principal DX code then Exclude.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Exclusions for the chronic condition of Stroke and Transient Ischemic Attack (TIA).),(Data Element Scope: Condition, Claim Diagnosis),(Inclusion Criteria: See specific codes),(Exclusion Criteria: n/a)
